<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Data Protection Alert</title>
</head>

<body style="margin:0; padding:0; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size:14px; color:#111111; line-height:1.25;">

  <div style="width:760px; margin:0 auto; padding:20px;">

    <!-- Blue Box -->
    <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="width:95px; height:95px; background-color:#01B0F1;">
      <tr>
        <td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle; color:#ffffff; font-weight:bold;">
          A Message
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table>

    <!-- Header -->
    <div style="font-size:30px; color:#00A0DF; margin-top:25px;">
      from SCS Cyber Operations
    </div>

    <!-- Title Bar -->
    <div style="background-color:#01B0F1; font-weight:bold; padding:4px; margin-top:18px;">
      Data Protection Alert – Unauthorized Service Account Use – Case [Case.Id]
    </div>

    <p>Hi [Event.event_principal_user_managers_1_userid],</p>

    <p>
      We identified recent <b>interactive use of a non-human identity (service account)</b> by a member of your team.
      Service accounts are intended for automated system use only and should not be used for individual logins
      (e.g., desktop access or direct database access).
    </p>

    <p><b>Details</b></p>

    <ul>
      <li><b>Service Account:</b> [event_target_user_userid]</li>
      <li><b>User:</b> [event_principal_user_userDisplayName]</li>
      <li><b>Last Detected Use:</b> [event_metadata_eventTimestamp]</li>
      <li><b>System/Environment:</b> [event_additional_database]</li>
    </ul>

    <p><b>Why this matters</b><br>
    Interactive use of service accounts:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>Obscures accountability for actions taken</li>
      <li>Bypasses key controls such as MFA and session monitoring</li>
      <li>Increases risk to systems and sensitive data</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      This activity is not permitted under the
      <a href="#" style="color:#006B8F; font-weight:bold;">Identity, Authentication, and Access Management Standard (STND_00341)</a>
      and/or the
      <a href="#" style="color:#006B8F; font-weight:bold;">Network Security Standard (STND_02781)</a>.
    </p>

    <p><b>What we need from you</b></p>

    <!-- Action Box -->
    <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%; border:1px solid #666;">
      <tr>
        <td style="width:80px; border-right:1px solid #666; padding:15px;"></td>
        <td style="padding:12px;">
          <p style="margin-top:0;"><b><u>Action Items</u></b></p>
          <p>
            Please ensure that <b>[event_principal_user_userDisplayName]</b> stops using this service account for
            <b>interactive access immediately.</b> Access should be performed using an individual (human) account.
            If additional access is required, it should be requested through
            <a href="#" style="color:#006B8F; font-weight:bold;">MyAccess</a>.
            System credentials are intended only for system-to-system authentication and should not be used by human users.
          </p>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table>

    <p><b>What happens next</b></p>

    <ul>
      <li>We will close this case and continue to monitor for this activity</li>
      <li>Continued use may result in access restriction or removal</li>
      <li>Repeated occurrences will be escalated to leadership and may result in the service account being disabled</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      If this service account is being used due to an access gap or tooling limitation, we can help resolve it quickly.
    </p>

    <p>
      Please reference platform-specific guidance in
      <a href="#" style="color:#006B8F;">Database Access Governance (DAG)</a>,
      or consult the following architecture resources:
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li><a href="#" style="color:#006B8F;"><i>System Credential Management Solution Selector (Schwab Architecture Library)</i></a></li>
      <li><a href="#" style="color:#006B8F;"><i>System Authentication Solution Selector (Schwab Architecture Library)</i></a></li>
    </ul>

    <p>Thank you for your prompt attention to this matter.</p>

    <p>
      _______________________<br>
      Data Protection Operations Team<br>
      Schwab Cybersecurity Services (SCS)
    </p>

  </div>

</body>
</html>
